Let me try a radically different approach. What if I change the assignment order? Instead of:
```ip = ...;
x20 = ...;
sa = ...;```

What if I do:```
ip = ...;sa = ...;
x20 = ...;
```

Since the asm loads x20 before sa, this might seem wrong. But MWCC might reorder the loads for scheduling even if the source has a different order (since there's no dependency between loading x20 and loading sa - both just read from ip).

